@node "Musical Misdemeanour"

                           MUSICAL MISDEMEANOUR.

QUESTION:-

        I have been told that the Amiga is no good for musical purposes as
it does not have a MIDI port. Is this true?

ANSWER:-
        Absolutely not! There are many MIDI (Musical Instruments Digital
Interface) adaptors available for the Amiga and it is rapidly becoming
widely used in a number of top studios. When a MIDI interface connected to
your Amiga, you can use your machine to control whole banks of synthesizers
using a variety if different software packages. One of the best packages
for the Amiga is Bars & Pipes Pro v2.0 which is what is known as a
'sequencer'. Also available for the  Amiga are a massive range of patch
editors and librarians. You don't have to own  MIDI equipment to create
music on your Amiga, however. Thanks to the Amiga's powerful sound chip,
you can create music using  your Amiga's own 4-channel sound capabilities.
All you need is a program like Deluxe Music 2.0 or even a PD like OctMed 5.



                             @{"     " link "main"} Return

@endnode

