@endnode

@node "Through the Window"

                            THROUGH THE WINDOW.

QUESTION:-

        I have been trying to copy programs from the workbench disk onto an
empty disk of my own. Unfortunately, when I moved the icons into the new
window they were placed on top of each other. Even if I expand the window
and move them about, the next time I open the window up they are back where
they started. How can I separate them?

ANSWER:-
        There is a way to make Workbench remember any changes you make to a
window, using the Snapshot option on the right menu at the top of the
screen. You probably need a bigger window, so the first thing to do is
expand it, and then, while the window is selected, select Snapshot.
Whenever the window is opened it will appear at this new size. Similarly,
you can move an icon to where you want it inside the window and take a
Snapshot of its new position. Bear in mind that the icon must be selected
for Snapshot to work. If you want to move more then one icon, you can
Snapshot each individually, or you can keep the shift key held down while
you use the mouse to select all of them and then do a single Snapshot.



